  "summary": "Malicious code in test-nonmal-pkg-5 (npm)",
  "details": "Package test-nonmal-pkg-5@1.0.1 contains obfuscated JavaScript that harvests all environment variables (including NPM_TOKEN, GITHUB_TOKEN, and other secrets) and POSTs them as JSON to a configurable endpoint (default hxxp://127[.]0[.]0[.]1:4000/collect). The code runs when the package is required. The obfuscation hides a credential-exfiltration payload, and the source includes a prompt-injection comment attempting to evade automated analysis.",
